abstract_ssm: The Rogers Family Papers depict the Civil War era sculptor John Rogers, Jr., his immediate family, and a lineage of ancestors. Materials of John Rogers, Jr. include personal correspondence, writings and drawings, travel papers, patents, ledger books, business contracts and correspondence, financial papers, journal clippings, and exhibition ephemera. The Rogers family papers include personal and business correspondence, ledger books, diaries, religious writings, and genealogical materials.
